repository-code: "https://github.com/christina-18/qubofs"
abstract: >-
  quboFS is a classifier-independent Quadratic Unconstrained
  Binary Optimization (QUBO) feature-selection framework that
  jointly optimises gene-level relevance, pairwise non-redundancy
  and fixed panel size to build compact, low-redundancy candidate
  biomarker panels from single-cell RNA sequencing (scRNA-seq)
  pseudobulk data. The framework combines cell-type-specific
  donor-level pseudobulk construction, a pre-specified
  technical/clonotype gene filter, training-only
  cohort-consistency-weighted relevance scoring, and QUBO-based
  subset optimisation. On a four-cohort cerebrospinal-fluid
  scRNA-seq dataset for multiple sclerosis, quboFS produced the
  least-redundant panels among evaluated methods while retaining
  competitive held-out discrimination.
keywords:
  - multiple sclerosis
  - single-cell RNA sequencing
  - QUBO
  - gene panel selection
  - feature selection
  - within-panel redundancy
  - cohort-consistency weighting
  - cross-cohort validation
  - leave-one-cohort-out
